  "text": "The models were built in TensorFlow, run from an Anaconda Python 3.6.6 environment. The TensorFlow version used is TensorFlow GPU 1.09. To enable GPU acceleration, NVIDIA CUDA 9.0, along with CuDNN 7, was used. The experiments were conducted on a Windows 10 PC with an NVIDIA GeForce GTX 850M GPU, an Intel Core i7-5500U CPU @ 2.40 GHz and 8 GB RAM. Other essential Python packages used in our Anaconda environment include NumPy, AstroPy, Scikit-image and PyDL. We use code that makes use of parts of the original AstroNet code [CITATION_1] , supplemented with our own code necessary for the implementation of our research. Links to our code and the original AstroNet code can be found in the Appendix.",
